Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.66,0:01:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's wonderful.\NGod appears and disappears on command.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.90,0:02:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I turned on?\NOh, good, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days I fall over, this morning I'm falling over,\Nso we have the chair for assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We always start the lectures\Nwith a very significant piece of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which can save you many lifetimes.\NNothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.59,0:02:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The primary illusion, the ignorance.\NAll the great avatars spoke of a basic ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.22,0:03:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't really define what the ignorance was,\Nto my satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.48,0:03:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic ignorance is, for the intelligent world,\Nof which we are a major component,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.66,0:03:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic belief in causality is the stumbling block.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.45,0:03:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people get beyond the 400s.\NEven Einstein didn't make it, 499, Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.44,0:03:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The great geniuses couldn't get beyond\Nthe great barrier of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.35,0:03:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of a separate, independent person,\Ndifferent and separate from God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on the whole axiom of causality.\NThere is nothing causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:04:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NAll comes into existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of divine ordination.\NThe unmanifest becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously,\Neffortlessly and perfectly,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as evolution is unfolding.\NCreation and evolution are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The great infinite energy field,\Nin which we all have our existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is happening spontaneously,\Neverything automatically fulfills its karmic potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all happening of its own, with absolute perfection.\NIt requires no outside agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:05:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That we say now is the advancing edge of evolution.\NWe are the product of all of evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NWe inherit a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is called that karma.\NWe can do without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do without karma.\NYou can just be what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You relax into it.\NThere is nothing to be acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.86,0:05:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing new.\NThere's only the relinquishment of that which you are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That requires no effort,\Nbut it requires merely a laying back
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.03,0:06:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowing things to be.\NSo where do you find the essence of divinity within you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God is both transcendent,\Nfrom a descriptive viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.90,0:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and imminent from an experiential.\NGod transcendent is the subject of theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God imminent is the subject of the mystic.\NJust as the scientist is the authority of the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.20,0:06:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the mystic is the authority of the nonlinear domain,\Nwhich is completely experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.53,0:06:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And about which nothing can be said.\NIt will take us all morning to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.67,0:06:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,how nothing need be said.\NWhere's the board?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.99,0:06:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Whiteboard.\NWhy did you cancel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.87,0:07:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you'll have to have the whiteboard.\NDo we have the whiteboard, Brock?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.66,0:07:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Brock, we have the whiteboard.\NWe can maybe get one from the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.21,0:07:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find God without an explanation,\Nyou understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a diagram.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.11,0:07:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are at the forefront.\NSo we are at the forefront.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.11,0:07:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We are at the forefront of the evolution of consciousness\Nas it has evolved through millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the epitome of it in this domain at this moment.\NWe all have within us a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.19,0:08:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Education is to inform us about the content\Nand has to do with the world of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.19,0:08:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual reality, which everyone seeks\Nwhen they reach a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they begin to intuit it.\NAnd then they get captivated,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.75,0:08:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they get captured by the gravity.\NThey get captured by the gravity of the potential
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of their own future.\NPeople think they're driven by the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.55,0:08:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not driven by the past.\NYou're attracted by the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the future has been set by your own intention.\NThe intention to become enlightened, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.38,0:08:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is why everybody is here\Nand why they're all gonna be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the desire to be enlightened,\Nyou can't be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.27,0:08:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the desire to be enlightened, you can't be enlightened.\NOnce the desire to be enlightened, you can't be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've heard of it, nothing else will suffice.\NOnce you've heard of it, nothing else will suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.37,0:08:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said that and that is a fact.\NThe Buddha said that and that is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.37,0:08:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked already,\NWhat's the difference between salvation and enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.40,0:08:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked already,\NWhat's the difference between salvation and enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.97,0:09:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between salvation and enlightenment?\NAs we said, much of what we say came about
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, much of what we say came about\Nnot only through subjective realization,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but then a verification by advanced techniques\Nof consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.70,0:09:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To an ignorant world, Christ came directly from Heaven,\Nwith no prior human knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.20,0:09:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in lifetimes to teach salvation that there was an infinite domain of spiritual reality\Nand he taught how to avoid what we can only call bad karma to avoid the lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:10:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is no death consequently when you leave the body you will really experience that\Nwhich you are that which you are is in a way self-created through one's own choice and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.23,0:10:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual intention so he said do not create for yourself once you leave the body regions of\Nsuffering and misery instead follow these teachings and you will experience the heavenly realms
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore the knowingness of that is already within you he said heaven is already within\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.76,0:10:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you and it is only necessary to discover it. So he led the way and showed the way\Nhow to discover it. The energy field of that which we call Jesus the Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.86,0:11:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 1,000 which is the highest dimension on our calibrated scale of\Nconsciousness. It is very unlikely that the human nervous system can handle an
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.56,0:11:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field over a thousand and even as it gets near there there's a tendency to\Nfall over and get weak and leave the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.09,0:11:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right so we'll try to what we're actually going to be doing is trying to\Nclarify what Christ said and as you will discover he said avoid anything that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go weak with kinesiology that's what he said because we discover\Nthen it calibrates below 200 and makes you go weak with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is precisely what has been what he defined as sin. So sin is not to be\Nfeared not to be dreaded not to be a source of guilt it's to be transcended
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.95,0:12:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoided because it's a road that leads you to unpleasant places. In this\Nexperiential infinity which is talking to you today there was the profound
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of the lower depths of hell and I agree with Jesus Christ.\NThey are to be avoided at all costs. Far more dreadful than can be imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because they are outside of time. It's one thing to have a migraine it's\Nanother have to have a migraine through all eternity. There's no imitrix in hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.23,0:12:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the spontaneous inner awareness that transformed this consciousness is\Nin total agreement with Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However he's saying in a way that this is a very difficult level. This is a very\Ndifficult planet for humans. Life is very difficult and the chance of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.28,0:13:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming completely enlightened are slim here because the gravity of our\Ncivilization is so powerful. As we finish as we get into the lecture today which
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.79,0:13:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually quite fascinating.\NYou know it's like you discovered EMC squared and you can't wait to show it to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.39,0:13:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody. The explanation of all of history you'll understand this morning.\NSo yes it's gonna be clear as a bell. So what Jesus said is the best thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.53,0:14:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is to from a practical viewpoint don't forget at the time of the birth of Jesus\Nthe calibrated level of consciousness of mankind was 100. At the time of the birth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Buddha was 90.\N100 uneducated tribes is what he was talking to. Couldn't read, spell, had no
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,schooling, illiterate, printing press hadn't been invented yet. You're talking to a\Nrelatively primitive society and he was also not appreciated for telling the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,truth.\NLet's have the calibrated level of consciousness. We ask was Jesus Christ put to death for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.52,0:14:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,telling the truth?\NThe answer is no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.38,0:15:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is yes. We corroborate everything we say. That's a fact. He was put to\Ndeath for telling the truth. In contrast, so what Jesus Christ said, I always forget
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.29,0:15:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,my pointer. I've got a gorgeous little light at home but I can't figure out how to use it.\NSo Jesus Christ, we never attended one of my classes but if he had he would have mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We were focused and...\NThank you. Alright. He said, avoid anything that calibrates below 200, that which is fallacious,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.02,0:16:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is prideful, angered, guilt, desire. Avoid coming out, I mean there's another\Nterminology, avoid coming out of the lower chakras. Strive at least in America so the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.13,0:16:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,solar plexus has gotten us where we are. Achievement, drive...\NThat's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great quote.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.25,0:16:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's a great quote.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.37,0:16:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.51,0:16:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.\NThat's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.83,0:16:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.01,0:16:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI love that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.19,0:16:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.25,0:16:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,greed, but then once you've achieved that, you have the courage to start looking for\Nthe truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.30,0:16:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So avoid anything that makes you go weak with kinesiology.\NWe have a culture, you know, which is devoted to promoting vulgarity, violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard, I saw a tape by Wayne Dyer the other day, he said that by the time the average\Nchild is 12 or 15, something like that, he's already witnessed 58,000 murders, hour after
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,hour.\NAnd then he turns off the killing on the television set and gets a video game which teaches him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.32,0:17:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,how to kill with greater technical capacity.\NThe outpouring of the negativity then is immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.87,0:17:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a society which calibrated at 90.\NHe said, well, I'm going to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, to strive for love, and the highest love is unconditional love.\NSo what he was really saying, the perfect Christian then strives for unconditional love,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the saint.\NTo strive for sainthood, and as we'll see when we finally get to some calibrations of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual teachers and all, that Christian sainthood characteristically does occur in\Nthe 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.54,0:18:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to reach 500 itself is reached by only 4% of the population, and unconditional\Nlove is reached by 0.4% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.92,0:18:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is practical and feasible in our world, he said, is if you avoid sin, and by meditation,\Nworship and forgiveness of others, strive to reach unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause from unconditional love, from love, from love, one goes to the higher celestial
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,realms, the heavens, when you leave the physical body.\NYou can turn that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha, however, had a different message.\NThe Buddha, although he was speaking in a society where the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.57,0:19:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world was only 90, he came from a pretty sophisticated background.\NEnlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.99,0:19:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment was already ancient in the Vedas, and therefore his audience, which was\Na more advanced spiritual audience, was capable of reaching for something higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha taught the way to enlightenment.\NSo as love is 500 to 540, enlightenment, when it occurs, is calibrated at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha himself went to advanced states of enlightenment, which practically never\Noccurred in history, to 1,000, its ultimate capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.42,0:20:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of divinity within, as the self, is a realization that occurs about 700.\NAnd that is a practical goal, to realize the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.11,0:20:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And in recent times, we use Ramana Maharshi and Nisargadatta Maharaj as examples, primarily\Nbecause they live sufficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.17,0:20:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, what they had to say has been taken down verbatim.\NWhat Jesus said and what the Buddha said, thousands of years ago, some of it is verifiable
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.19,0:20:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and some of it is not, which we'll get into today.\NEnlightenment is therefore, you might say, a more ambitious undertaking, and it requires
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.01,0:20:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a more intense commitment.\NWhat we teach?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.62,0:21:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What it's given we have called, devotional non-duality.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, to reach enlightenment one has to transcend duality.\NAnd to do that takes a great devotion, a great devotion to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.90,0:21:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not devotion to some other being, but devotion to the essence of the truth itself, which\Nis already within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.42,0:21:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It means, under appropriate conditions with great intention, one can filamentate it and\Nreach a very advanced state of consciousness even within this world therefore both salvation and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.21,0:22:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment are possibilities practical possibilities doable except that you don't do it\Nso how to find the way all right the most direct way is to my studies understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.54,0:22:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and experiences devotional non-duality why because god cannot be experienced in as a past entity so\Ntraditional religion will tell you what happened on the other side of the world with some other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.90,0:22:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ethnic group 2 000 years ago under peculiar conditions and how does that help you now\Nif you're waiting for the bus that's very interesting historically and that has been
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of the way of religion is to\Nwhat should we say not academic but um to put in a rigid form historical events
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.29,0:23:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to who where and when backwards in time gets into sort of a deification of geography\Nand historic events most of which were more political than spiritual in the first place
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.65,0:23:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,however innate within religion is spiritual truth and some people are\Ncapable of ignoring the trivialities and focusing on the central truth when people reach a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.76,0:23:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness however they begin seeking the core of spiritual truth for its own sake\Nwhat is the ultimate reality that is realizable and they begin to seek what is traditionally
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.14,0:24:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,called self-realization the awareness that the source of your own existence is within\Ntherefore if the discovery is something within there's no point of looking for it in history
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.46,0:24:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or elsewhere there is nothing new to be acquired no new knowledge no new experience it's a matter of\Nsurrendering to what already exists so what needs to be realized that which people are looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.36,0:24:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is already an existent reality and one's devotion to letting go of polygamy and the\Nspiritualaniy of the soul of god
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all the obstacles, which is devotional,\Nis letting go all judgmentalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.72,0:24:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all considerations, all dualistic,\Nthis versus that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.01,0:25:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowing which already exists.\NThe most profound awareness as it unfolds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.77,0:25:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is that divinity is the very source of your existence.\NSo the fast track is to look back of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.76,0:25:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to try to sense and intuit\Nthe source out of which your existence arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.41,0:25:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the source out of which all phenomena arise\Nis an infinite, is a potentiality becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.92,0:25:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you see, everything is happening spontaneously\Nand perfectly of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.50,0:25:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NThe belief in cause will fix you in an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.92,0:25:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a subconsciousness,\Na separate I, the ego self,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.19,0:26:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that is separate from the infinite I.\NSo the whole belief system of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.02,0:26:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is why most people never transcend the 400th.\NEverything is happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.68,0:26:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the fact that it is manifesting\Nits potential, its karmic inheritance,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.21,0:26:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilling its potentiality.\NThis is all a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.80,0:26:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all occurring in an infinite universe\Nof infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.98,0:26:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe which we call consciousness,\Nwhich is beyond form,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:27:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear domain beyond form,\Nis the source of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.45,0:27:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even within the physical domain,\None cubic centimeter of space
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.76,0:27:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,contains an infinite amount of power.\NThe potential power in one cubic centimeter,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.60,0:27:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of space, is infinite.\NTherefore, the field, the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.33,0:27:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of power within the universe.\NAnd a field exerts its dominance, its power,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.07,0:27:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by merely being what it is,\Nto merely be that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.23,0:27:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything within it, like little iron filings,\Nautomatically moves in a karmic dance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.27,0:28:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own potentiality.\NThere is no other to be feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.62,0:28:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no other to be dreaded.\NThe infinite field, then, dominates all within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.04,0:28:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the context, the infinite source of existence.\NWithin, then, the source of joy is not out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.97,0:28:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of joy, then, is the witnessing,\Nthe realization, the experience, the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.97,0:28:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of your existence is the source of joy.\NAnd it is the same source,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.99,0:28:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as the devotion,\Nwhich drives you through the obstacles of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.30,0:29:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend the ego, then,\None can save an infinite number of lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.37,0:29:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by letting go of the theory of causality.\NBefore we genuflect before the theory of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.51,0:29:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see what it calibrates.\NIt calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.84,0:29:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is over 460.\N465.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.90,0:29:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,470.\NThe principle of causality is 470.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.67,0:29:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That is wonderful for operating in the world.\NIt's science.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.16,0:29:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's logic.\NBut 470 is a long, long way from enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.55,0:29:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At 470, you read about it.\NAs we'll see, the great churches,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.70,0:29:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they started out at 1,000,\Nand then over time came down into the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.76,0:30:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They did so because they were trying to explain\Nit, to explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.14,0:30:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience is way beyond 400.\NIn fact, nothing is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.52,0:30:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As the realization of the source of your experience,\Nyou realize it's the divinity that is the source
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.00,0:30:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the isness of all that exists.\NAnd it just reveals itself in an enormous overwhelm,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.34,0:30:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which takes you out of the world for some time.\NI don't know how you get back into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.62,0:30:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say here's a person with a small essence,\Na small self,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.07,0:30:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and here we're going to make the universe,\Nsort of a mini-universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.56,0:31:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can't see, which is good.\NWhere do I get hung up on form?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.53,0:31:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think somebody washed this with a nice high-gloss polish.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.53,0:31:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there we have the ego, the world of form.\NAnd here we have, with little dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.69,0:31:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite universe.\NSo we can save huge amounts of time
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.52,0:31:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by understanding what this is all about.\NThis is the world of form,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.25,0:31:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which we witness every day,\Nwhich we identify with as the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.44,0:31:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the self, with a small s.\NThis infinite potentiality is the self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.05,0:31:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person thinks,\NI am this, and ignores this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.42,0:31:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person thinks my survival is this.\NWhen it's due to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.87,0:31:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's actually due to this.\NYour existence is supported by the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.24,0:32:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the best efforts of your ego,\Nwhich it looks for praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.33,0:32:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered the keys to the house today.\NWhat a good boy am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.52,0:32:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I remember the keys to the house?\NBecause the spirit, which sustains my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.52,0:32:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is a field,\Nwhich tends to bring that kind of self-preservation thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.52,0:32:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,up out of the ego, see,\Nwithout
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.32,0:32:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite field,\Nthe mind would have had no reason
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.02,0:32:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to remember the keys to the house.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.49,0:32:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When one lets go thinking that I am this,\Nso you see how causality works.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.49,0:32:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality thinks there is a personal I\Nthat is the cause of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.49,0:32:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or there's something out there\Nthat is the cause of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.78,0:32:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,\Nthe average lifetime is spent
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.13,0:33:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,manipulating and struggling\Nin the world of duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.41,0:33:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the world of force,\Nbased on the idea of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.70,0:33:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With the transcendence of identification with this,\None begins to intuit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.91,0:33:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a higher field,\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.87,0:33:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the letting go of the identification with this itself\Nleads to the identification of this itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.93,0:33:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we tell people,\Nif you're serious about spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.85,0:33:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure you have friends that know that.\NHa ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.85,0:33:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that in some lecture,\Nand I got a worried letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.29,0:33:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we do that, you know?\NBecause intense meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.52,0:33:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,plus really merely hearing of higher truth,\Ncan transport you rather rapidly past
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.52,0:33:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels of the ego,\Nand you find yourself in a state
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.68,0:34:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that can only be described as what?\NClassically, it's called bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.46,0:34:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In that state, one really,\Nfrom a physical viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.92,0:34:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is relatively immobilized.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.87,0:34:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the volition has gone out of,\Nout of running it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.04,0:34:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not me,\Nit becomes like a piece of furniture
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.04,0:34:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of no particular interest.\NOther people may entreat you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.07,0:34:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to come back in the body and reactivate it,\Nand it's best to ignore them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.80,0:34:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They think you've died, let them grieve it.\NBecause there is no death.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.91,0:34:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not possible for life\Nto cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.96,0:35:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the conservation of energy of matter\Nand energy applies to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.15,0:35:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is the source,\Nthe very source and essence of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.40,0:35:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,can hardly have a beginning or an end.\NThat which is all-encompassing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.36,0:35:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,can only transform from this into that,\Nbut it cannot cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.36,0:35:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not have the power within itself\Nto create its own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.80,0:35:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,nor does it have within itself\Nthe option to cease its own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.80,0:35:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because the source and the control of existence\Ndoes not belong to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.54,0:35:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't belong to you.\NYou're not going to have any say about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.65,0:35:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside of that is\Nyou don't get to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.58,0:36:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,even your own physical death.\NAs I said, the karmic destination
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.09,0:36:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is already set at the time of birth.\NThe time of death is already set.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.02,0:36:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As people are born,\Nthey already have a calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.89,0:36:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So if people don't believe in karma,\Nthey will have to explain that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.11,0:36:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However, then we know that the spirit\Nenters the embryo in the third month.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.91,0:36:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you're born with a calibrated level of consciousness\Nright from birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.52,0:36:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit, the entity from our own consciousness research,\Nenters the embryo at age three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.52,0:36:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After that time, it waits to see\Nif it's going to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.52,0:36:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This bus is going to get there\Nbefore it gets on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.60,0:36:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the time of expiration of this physicality\Nis already set at the time of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.60,0:36:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The time of birth is already set.\NAt that particular event,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.80,0:37:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not possible to experience one's physical death\Nbecause you're instantly out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.12,0:37:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You witnessed the physicality down there\Nand you didn't die at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.53,0:37:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's disappointing for a lot of people.\NEverything we said.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.97,0:37:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We verify anything that may be\Nsomewhat in conflict with popular belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.97,0:37:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if what I'm saying isn't in conflict\Nwith many belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.60,0:37:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know I'm lying.\NBecause if the truth were prevalent,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.17,0:37:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody would be enlightened.\NIt's extremely rare, consequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.29,0:37:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world believes primarily\Nis primarily fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.38,0:37:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of the world\Nwas 190 until the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.38,0:37:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when it suddenly jumped to 207.\NAnd so, it's a new level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.32,0:38:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of mankind.\NWith profound implications for life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.89,0:38:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, here on this planet.\NTherefore, nothing that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.28,0:38:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,has a cause.\NEverything is coming about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.85,0:38:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as the advancing edge\Nof creation, evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.32,0:38:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as the spontaneous interaction\Nof all that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.44,0:38:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,both linear and non-linear,\Nback through infinite time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.36,0:38:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinite\Nhas no beginning nor end.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.64,0:39:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One time a student in the back of the classroom\Nsaid,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.48,0:39:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher, teacher,\Nwhen did you say the world was ending?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.68,0:39:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher said,\Na hundred trillions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.84,0:39:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, oh my god,\NI thought you said a hundred billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.87,0:39:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what most people worry about.\NThe trivial idiocies and irrelevancies of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.87,0:39:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And many religions fall into that.\NThey're more worried about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.87,0:39:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of shoelaces to wear,\Nand whether they wear a hat
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.87,0:39:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or don't wear a hat.\NAnd completely ignore
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.87,0:39:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the crucial spiritual truth, you know.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.38,0:39:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll look at the sad story\Nof the world's religions in a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.44,0:39:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just have\Nthe Calvary level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.22,0:39:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to just reaffirm,\Nwith kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.72,0:39:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anything from here down\Nmakes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.72,0:39:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything from here up\Nmakes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.93,0:40:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The response\Nis an impersonal response
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.57,0:40:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NConsciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.02,0:40:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is an expression of life,\Nand life recognizes truth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.02,0:40:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is.\NAnd it fails to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.14,0:40:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is adverse to life\Nand which has no intrinsic reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.14,0:40:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore the arm goes weak.\NThe theory of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.09,0:40:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,also calibrates around 460.\NSo it's an explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.41,0:40:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which satisfies the intellect.\NBut a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.02,0:40:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your problem is not your intellect.\NThe problem is to transcend the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.47,0:40:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already arrived\Nat a very advanced level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.79,0:40:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the high,\Nmost people are in the,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.79,0:40:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,considerably into the 400s.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.62,0:40:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll just continue that.\NAnd then we'll go on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.62,0:40:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to some more interesting things.\NLet's do that next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.52,0:41:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just recapitulating\Nprevious lectures here
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.52,0:41:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for people who haven't been here before.\NAnd because we all want to start out
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.55,0:41:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same place.\NWe said that the basic principle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.80,0:41:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the divisive factor\Nthat keeps the ego going
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.80,0:41:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is its capacity to think\Nin terms of duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.70,0:41:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway of devotional non-duality\Nthen is,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.70,0:41:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,means how to transcend\Ndualistic thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.99,0:41:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Either or,\Ngood and bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.99,0:41:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,war and peace.\NAs we demonstrated
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.02,0:41:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in previous lectures,\Nwar is not the opposite of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.02,0:41:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Npeace is the opposite of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.66,0:41:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of creating\Nartificial dualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.66,0:41:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which exist only as mentations\Nwithin the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.92,0:41:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These dualities are only a mentation.\NAnd to demonstrate this,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.89,0:41:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we point that opposite,\Nthat hot is not the opposite of cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.08,0:42:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are varying degrees\Nof the presence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.15,0:42:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's arbitrary to say\Nthis is hot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.15,0:42:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's quite obvious\Nthey're not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.15,0:42:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable.\NAnd that's a fact
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.40,0:42:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in all dualistic thinking.\NThere's actually only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.81,0:42:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In linguistic convenience,\Nwe have divided it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.96,0:42:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But in fact,\Nthere is no such reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.70,0:42:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has absolute reality\Ncan only be proven subjectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.99,0:42:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nthe newest book is called
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.99,0:42:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I,\NReality and Subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.52,0:42:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because reality can only be known\Nas subjectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.58,0:42:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So dualistic is a way of talking about it,\Nbut it's not a way of being it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.19,0:42:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's use value.\NYou can see again,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.19,0:42:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this has to do with\Nhow it looks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.22,0:42:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the opposite of this.\NAnd what somebody thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.44,0:43:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is an ugly-looking alley\Ncan look to somebody else
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.44,0:43:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,like an artistic presentation.\NOkay, so we're done with all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.73,0:43:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we...\NOh, I wanted to show
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.89,0:43:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the last one in this one.\NThis is a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.89,0:43:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we've done now\Nis recapitulate how we got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.04,0:43:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a girl\Nat the girl's rehab place that I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.30,0:43:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And all she says is,\NI want out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.30,0:43:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want out of here.\NI want out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.30,0:43:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want out of here.\NAll our girls say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.30,0:43:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I want out of here.\NI want out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.46,0:43:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I want out of here.\NSo I made her draw this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.46,0:43:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And she actually did this freehand.\NI said,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.46,0:43:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what you want.\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.46,0:43:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I want out of here.\NGive me them bananas.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.46,0:43:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said,\NLook how you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.46,0:43:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The harder you reach for the bananas,\Nthe tighter you are against the bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.46,0:43:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you shout,\Nyell,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.46,0:43:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,hit people,\Ncut yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.46,0:43:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,threaten people,\Nyou can see you're tightening your imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.84,0:43:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually you're going to flatten yourself\Nup against the bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.04,0:44:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do.\NCompletely paralyzed by their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.54,0:44:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is the unsophisticated basis of the ego.\NThe I want,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.76,0:44:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the grabbing this,\Nwhich comes out of the animal evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.24,0:44:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said,\NSo I said to the girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.49,0:44:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize\Nthat the door to the cage is over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.49,0:44:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is freedom.\NYou have to turn your back
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.81,0:44:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on the solar plexus demanding this,\Nof I wanting this,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.32,0:44:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and become what this place is for.\NTo learn how to behave,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.93,0:44:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to control yourself,\Nlearn how to be responsible,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.93,0:44:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,learn something of the milk of human kindness.\NAnd then the door is open to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.73,0:44:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\NThe door is open all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.73,0:44:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The door has never been closed.\NAnd of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.99,0:45:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when they reach a certain level of improvement,\Nthey're automatically discharged.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.99,0:45:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\Nthey can't even stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.99,0:45:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Their agency pulls them out.\NSo this is the way it is with enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.33,0:45:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not something you can reach for\Nand strive to get,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.59,0:45:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is already a reality\Nand the door is already open.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.72,0:45:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSo that was her contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.55,0:45:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She did it freehand,\Nand I thank her for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.96,0:45:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I made many copies for it.\NI knew I'd use it someday for something,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.96,0:45:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and this morning it came up.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.02,0:45:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody knows the way to enlightenment now.\NIt's merely a surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.18,0:45:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of all opinionation, positionalities.\NAnd remember this, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.72,0:45:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgmentalism is bad.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.79,0:46:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the circuitous way the ego can grab you, you know.\NI got a letter from a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.92,0:46:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,\NWhy do you use bad language?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.92,0:46:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NDid she say bad language?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.92,0:46:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, bad language.\NWell, I never heard myself use bad language.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.10,0:46:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all,\NI don't know what's going to be said
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.10,0:46:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,until I hear it myself.\NSo she goes to a lecture on non-duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.88,0:46:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go of judgmentalism,\Nand tells me my speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.98,0:46:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I use bad language.\NI've got to get a kick out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.28,0:46:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the bad language about?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.28,0:46:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got our perceptions.\NAt the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.76,0:46:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain I thought it was good.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.28,0:46:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's men and women,\Nyou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.28,0:46:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And what sounds meaningful\Nand sinks home with a woman
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.38,0:46:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to a guy who's going to say,\NMan, that was really airy-fairy, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.38,0:47:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NIt's all peaches and cream and flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.96,0:47:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and it sounds sweet.\NBut what about the real world?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.34,0:47:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So occasionally,\NI use language that's masculine
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.34,0:47:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because it pulls out of your gut\Nthat that's crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.34,0:47:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NThat word gets,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.34,0:47:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get what you mean, see?\NI could say it's inadvisable.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.96,0:47:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not totally acceptable.\NLast night,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.31,0:47:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they had the History Channel,\Nthe story of Ivan the Terrible,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.31,0:47:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the worst stories in history.\NI looked at Susie and I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.76,0:47:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,His behavior was not really too desirable, Susie.\NNow, occasionally,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.81,0:47:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to speak to the masculine\Nbecause there's a gut way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.29,0:47:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nthat the woman doesn't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.29,0:47:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a glance between two guys,\Nand in that,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.52,0:48:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a complete understanding,\Na whole culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.52,0:48:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what it is.\NThis is your moment to climb the mast, Shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.86,0:48:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're terrified is your crap, boy.\NActually, Shorty didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.18,0:48:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He got to the top and had to be rescued.\NBut the guy knows what that means, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.47,0:48:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it isn't a woman's language.\NSo when the guy goes like that with his foot,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.72,0:48:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it already has a meaning in his culture\Nand his background.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.72,0:48:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the woman goes like this,\Nthat has a meaning in her culture and background.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.98,0:48:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I spent a lot of time learning about those things.\NI'll say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.56,0:48:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that's insignificant tripe.\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.56,0:49:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's where they live.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.53,0:49:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll say,\Nbut that kind of a remark is,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.14,0:49:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nthis and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.14,0:49:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say,\Nyeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.14,0:49:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's where men live.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.14,0:49:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you will have to forgive me for using\Nthe best bad language I can think of at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.07,0:49:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My function is to communicate.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.07,0:49:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nit isn't a,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.42,0:49:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a doingness.\NIt's a,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.52,0:49:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,\Nit happens of its own anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.92,0:49:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\NI can't be responsible for what's said anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.92,0:49:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's said until it's said.\NI want to watch the time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.20,0:49:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because we've got a lot of tremendous stuff\Nto cover this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.20,0:49:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather earth-shaking and,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.43,0:49:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we better get to the earth-shaking world.\NLet's start with the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.43,0:50:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\NI've been working for,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.43,0:50:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,some months,\Nas soon as I've been working.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.43,0:50:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated the level of consciousness\Nof every country in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.43,0:50:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We then proceeded to do every continent.\NWe then proceeded to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.97,0:50:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,now,\Nso for simple explanation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.45,0:50:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,almost all of history and current events\Nsuddenly becomes obvious to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.54,0:50:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that man has been trying to navigate\Nwithout a compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.40,0:50:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How diplomatic course,\Nhow countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.40,0:50:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how statesmen can deal with each other\Nwhen they don't even know
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.40,0:50:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what they're dealing with is beyond me.\NIt would lead to endless catastrophe,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.40,0:50:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,war, revolution,\Nand of course it has.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.76,0:50:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Njust like the invention of the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.39,0:50:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed amazing discoveries,\Nor E equals MC squared,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.39,0:50:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,allows amazing discoveries,\Nsome discoveries are seminal
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.39,0:51:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and open up whole dimensions.\NHere we have the Western Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.93,0:51:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated the level of the consciousness\Nof these particular areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.93,0:51:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it's big enough that you can all see it.\NAnyway, we look up at Greenland and 345.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.44,0:51:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Iceland, I think, is somewhat less than that.\NThey have a lot of alcoholism there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think half the population is alcoholic in Iceland.\NSo that would be why it's somewhat lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.44,0:51:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at North America,\Nyou see Canada's about five points,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.44,0:51:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,10 points less than the United States.\NBut the general area you see is 410 to 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.44,0:51:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's education,\Nthat's science,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.51,0:51:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's reason,\Nrationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.51,0:51:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the laws we live by\Nand we presume everybody else lives by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.92,0:51:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get to the Central America,\Nthe 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.92,0:51:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enthusiasm,\Nbuilding big cement plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.14,0:52:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impressive what they do.\NThat's industry and forthrightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.33,0:52:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got South America.\NIt runs generally 285 to 310.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.75,0:52:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important of all this is it's all over 200.\NIt's all over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.75,0:52:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you're relatively safe.\NPeople may screw up down here with the Falkland Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.75,0:52:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to put them in.\NDue to some mad person,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.94,0:52:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's just bad judgment.\NIt's not a violently explosive hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.20,0:52:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You've only got one place here you've got to worry about\Nand they're too weak and at the bottom of the barrel
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.23,0:52:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to worry about them yet.\NBut they're at 55 and that's Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.23,0:52:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Haiti can't do much about it.\NSo when you pour more money into Haiti,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.92,0:52:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing that happens is the birth rate goes up\Nand poverty and starvation goes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.92,0:52:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So something other than cash,\Nwhich has been tried and everybody decided
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.34,0:52:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't help any.\NThose kind of people are also quite subject to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.50,0:53:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,sadistic rule by a dictator.\NA sadistic dictator.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.66,0:53:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I don't know anything about the history of Haiti,\NI'll tell you this place is probably
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.69,0:53:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,currently or recently run\Nby a sadistic dictator
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.69,0:53:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who exploits the people,\Nallows them to starve
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.69,0:53:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably just kills them for amusement.\NWhich is probably pretty accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.69,0:53:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, where's the next one?\NNow we'll get to more serious considerations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.94,0:53:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at the other hemisphere.\NWe saw Australia 410, intelligent, rational, educated.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.25,0:53:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we start getting up higher.\NYou see Korea in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.86,0:53:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan, they're all pretty good.\NIndia, 355.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.89,0:53:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you see Madagascar, 125.\NSouth Africa, 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.89,0:53:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you see the real trouble coming up.\NHere is all of Africa, about 40 to 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.56,0:54:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And North Africa, 70 to 185.\NAnd we will see the difficulty arises
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.30,0:54:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,between latitude 10 to 40 north\Nin North Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.30,0:54:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is where you're going to see all the problems.\NYou see Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.52,0:54:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see Mongolia,\Nyou see China at 305,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.52,0:54:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan at 355.\NThis is your...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.35,0:54:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is up there.\NSomething.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.80,0:54:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we've got maps with greater detail.\NI tried to simplify it so you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.80,0:54:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at North Africa about 175\Nand you're looking at the Near East.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.80,0:54:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go on to the next one.\NHow much will democracy appeal
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.87,0:54:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to people who calibrated 55?\NThey haven't even got water.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.54,0:54:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have bathrooms.\NYou don't have food.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.83,0:54:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your children are dying,\Nfalling over with AIDS and starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.08,0:55:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is interested in political systems?\NThey will naturally follow anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.23,0:55:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who gives them food and water.\NIt's easy to become a dictator.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.85,0:55:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You just steal from the weak\Nand use that to control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.65,0:55:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you give it back to them for a trickle\Nand in turn for their worship and servitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.65,0:55:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here we have this again.\NNo, let's...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.12,0:55:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the next one?\NOh, there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.44,0:55:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is too complicated, so...\NThe original of this took me a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.44,0:55:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It took us a week, right?\NA whole weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.50,0:55:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we calibrated every country in the world.\NYou see, I took the names of the countries out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.50,0:55:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because you wouldn't be able to read anything.\NBut now you can see what you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.92,0:55:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're in the State Department\Nand you say we're going to deal with
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.92,0:56:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,such and such country in such and such region,\Nyou better know what the hell you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.19,0:56:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated level of consciousness 70\Nhas nothing to do with 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.19,0:56:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with it.\NThey slaughter each other here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.05,0:56:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They just slaughter each other.\NThey're not even up to slavery yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.23,0:56:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery, 70 you get,\Nthe people just vanquished are worth money on the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.23,0:56:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These people aren't even there yet.\NThey just slaughter them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.23,0:56:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They take over a village.\NThey kill everybody in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.32,0:56:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's North Africa.\NAnd you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.38,0:56:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe is in the 300s,\N340s, 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.38,0:56:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the big problem areas of the world.\NSo if you don't know anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.89,0:56:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,don't read the newspaper at all,\Nand you look at this, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.89,0:56:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,uh-oh, I can see where the problems\Nare likely to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.02,0:56:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was embarrassed by\Nthe way an American interviewer
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.95,0:57:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,interviewed the President of China.\NPresident of China, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.65,0:57:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is much higher than 305,\Nway up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.88,0:57:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Insulting, saying to him,\Nlook what's wrong with your culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.16,0:57:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,civil rights and all that.\NIdiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.54,0:57:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Antagonizing the people\Nacting like we're better than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.54,0:57:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NThat isn't the way to make friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.83,0:57:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have the next\Nsad story here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.84,0:57:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now\Nthat you got the overall picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.84,0:57:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because people ask me,\Nwhat the names of the various countries are,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.91,0:57:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, so I put this up.\NIf you want the names of the countries, ask me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.00,0:57:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sudan, 70.\NRwanda, 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.12,0:57:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenya, 70.\NTanzania, 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.21,0:57:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Zambia, 110.\NAngola, 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.37,0:58:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Namibia, 100.\NZimbabwe, 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.82,0:58:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Botswana, 65.\NNigeria, 75.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.27,0:58:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Chad, 90.\NLook at the size of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.27,0:58:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethiopia,\None something or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.19,0:58:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Somalia, 100.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.21,0:58:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's North Africa.\NNow let's look up to an even sadder story.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.50,0:58:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Middle East.\NHere you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.79,0:58:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are not a danger to the world.\NAt 50, you can't get your act together.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.79,0:58:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have hardly clothes to wear.\NYou're not much of a danger to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.25,0:58:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But now,\Nwhen you start rising up a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.25,0:58:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting a little bit of power,\Nyou give people with a caveman mentality
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.25,0:58:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a gun, now you've got problems.\NWho are you giving a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.76,0:58:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People with a mentality up in here.\N180, 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.15,0:59:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll find,\Noh, look over on the right, I got it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.15,0:59:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the current calibration?\NWe change these calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.24,0:59:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from time to time.\NAs of maybe a week ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.63,0:59:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where it all was a week ago.\NIsrael, 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.63,0:59:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Palestine, 165.\NSaudi Arabia, 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.63,0:59:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Iraq, 160.\NUnited Arab Emirates, 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.72,0:59:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jordan, 185.\NIran, 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.72,0:59:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Iraq, 125.\NSyria, 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.13,0:59:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only hope in the region, Turkey, 245.\NNow you tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.04,0:59:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what good a peace parade will do.\NLet's have the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.99,0:59:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one was this week's Time Magazine.\NWhile I was doing all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.05,1:00:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we just reached its completion\Nthis week.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.66,1:00:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I opened Time Magazine,\Nthey must have had spies.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.70,1:00:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,From 10 to 40 degrees\Nnorth latitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.72,1:00:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,10 to 40 degrees north latitude.\NWhich is what I said already, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.75,1:00:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the question is,\Nshould the missionaries go in and,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.45,1:00:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, that was the topic.\NHere are exactly the same countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.45,1:00:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the same war area.\NIt's all
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.57,1:00:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,mind with potential\Nproblems. The question was,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.62,1:00:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,should the Christian missionaries go in there\Nand convert these people?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.29,1:00:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Which I thought was hysterically funny.\NBecause they'll get executed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.55,1:00:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for doing so, but aside from that,\Nit brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.55,1:00:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the corollary.\NShouldn't the Islamic people be over in America
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.58,1:01:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to convert us to Islam?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.49,1:01:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talk about spiritual\Ncommunity, we want to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.58,1:01:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the world, the condition of the world?\NWe're in it, but not of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.56,1:01:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do\Ndirectly? Well, if you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.38,1:01:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,deal with,\Nif you deal with this invisible
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.57,1:01:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,diagram here,\Nif you come at it directly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.92,1:01:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the difficulty you're going to have.\NTo use force, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.21,1:01:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to have a limited response.\NIt's not going to transform
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.91,1:01:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the people and turn them into\Nsaintly peaceniks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.91,1:01:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They make their living by war.\NThey get their status from war.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.80,1:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They get their sense of\Nmasculinity, sufficiency.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.84,1:02:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And even now, their spiritual\Nbelief system is just tied up
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.99,1:02:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with violence.\NTherefore, it does not seem to me
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.04,1:02:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that addressing it directly is going to have\Nvery salutary
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.04,1:02:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,results.\NIf you can't approach
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.72,1:02:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing with force in the level\Nof form, then how
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.78,1:02:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can you transform\Nit? Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.55,1:02:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by addressing the level\Nof power, not the level of force.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.55,1:02:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go in there and try to force\Nyou to change your belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.55,1:02:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and force you to adopt mind,\Nand if I don't,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.71,1:02:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't,\NI'll execute you,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.77,1:02:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to have a very limited benefit.\NAlright, so if I want to influence
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.24,1:02:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,something that is not touchable,\Nyou can't really touch that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.24,1:03:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,system, can you? You can't really touch it\Nwithout it blowing back at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.92,1:03:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Force creates counter-force.\NSo you're not going to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.55,1:03:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,save the world. What can\Nwe do then, as a spiritual community,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.96,1:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if we are all one as humans,\Nis by letting go
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.38,1:03:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,our own egoistic positionalities,\Nwe reinforce
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.41,1:03:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the field.\NAlright, by quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.80,1:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have that formula with us today.\NIf you don't behave, I'll get it out and show it to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.00,1:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics, we showed\Nthat the collapse of the wave function,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.00,1:03:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by the collapse of the wave function,\Nby spiritual intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.28,1:03:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,via the Heisenberg principle,\Nand Neumann manifestation of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.28,1:03:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as a collapse of the wave function,\Nwe change the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.35,1:03:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We change the field.\NSo let's say
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.92,1:03:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,human-ness is highly\Nvisible as structure,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.92,1:04:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,this thing-ness here,\Nwhich is behaving very well today.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.49,1:04:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There is this thing-ness here,\Nand then around it we could say
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.41,1:04:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,there's mentalization as we advance.\NThe animal doesn't do much in the way of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.41,1:04:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalization, but as he gets\Nmore advanced, he gets more mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.08,1:04:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he gets intuitive knowingness.\NAnd some animals
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.15,1:04:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,get to be pretty advanced.\NSome animals
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.66,1:04:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,get more advanced than humans.\NNot intellectually,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.72,1:04:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but spiritually.\NAs I said in the book, you're safer with Coco,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.04,1:04:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the gorilla,\Nthan you are with any of these people from the Near East.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.20,1:04:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco will not turn on you,\Nwill not deceive you, will not lie to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.86,1:04:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,will not kill you.\NWhen you turn your back, you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.37,1:04:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're capable of being honest.\NThere's that famous African
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.68,1:04:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,gray parrot\Nat the University in
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.74,1:05:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Arizona, too.\NAlso very honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.00,1:05:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't get it to lie.\NBlue ball, red sponge,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.06,1:05:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,soap.\NIncapable of deception.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.06,1:05:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThen we get mentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.05,1:05:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We get up to the 400s, we get mentation.\NSo you can say there's an energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.05,1:05:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,not physical.\NIt registers in the physical and activates the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.05,1:05:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain is a response\Nsystem to energy fields, and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.30,1:05:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a\Nreceiver of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.28,1:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,thought forms.\NThe thought forms are extremely high frequency,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.28,1:05:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,not reduplicable\Nwithin the physical realm,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.57,1:05:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but sufficiently powerful\Nto activate neuronal
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.05,1:05:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,imprinting and\Nmemorization, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.24,1:05:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nintelligence then and mentation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.65,1:06:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,creates like another field around this.\NAnd then comes spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.65,1:06:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first one\Nidentifies here, then here, then
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.94,1:06:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,here, then identifies with this here.\NWhen you stop identifying
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.80,1:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with this and identify with\Nthe field, you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.80,1:06:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of your own existence\Nbecause at 600, one goes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.80,1:06:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,into a state of profound bliss.\NEverything is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.86,1:06:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no words.\NThere is no other.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.05,1:06:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only the allness\Nof an infinite, exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.59,1:06:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,presence as\Nthe very essence of love itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.59,1:06:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is\Nthe end of the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.04,1:06:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing to do at that point,\Nseeing as you've lost interest in breathing,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.04,1:07:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is to forget about it.\NThe bliss state at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.93,1:07:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we say to people\Nthat are serious about spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.09,1:07:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,let people that are somewhat spiritually\Nsophisticated be aware, and
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.09,1:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you go into such a state,\Nthey should just smile at you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.18,1:07:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray with you\Nand be happy for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.10,1:07:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, they may call the police,\Nthey may call the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.10,1:07:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they may call for a psychiatrist,\Nwho won't know what the heck it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.26,1:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As it approaches,\Nit becomes like euphoria.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.60,1:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a gladness, a happiness, a joy.\NAnd this can reach
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.92,1:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,states of high ecstasy.\NSo one can also go into states
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.92,1:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of high ecstasy,\Nwhich can be confused with
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.98,1:07:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,mania, religious mania.\NSo I think in the last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.17,1:07:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave two columns,\Nhow to differentiate a true spiritual state
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.17,1:07:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from various psychiatric conditions.\NAnd when I was a consultant
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.17,1:08:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to many dioceses,\NCatholic and Episcopal
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.65,1:08:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and Zen monastery and all,\Nthey would sometimes send a monk to me
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.65,1:08:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they didn't know, is this guy enlightened\Nor is he catatonic?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.03,1:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be hard to tell that for an unsophisticated layman,\Nthey wouldn't know the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.35,1:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And having gone into such states,\Nalso I could see where the police
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.02,1:08:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would come and get you\Nand you just sit on this rock
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.02,1:08:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no reason to move\Nand the state is complete.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.69,1:08:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the completeness of the state.\NThere is no desire or thought
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.69,1:08:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to do or be anything else\Nthan what is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.69,1:08:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is total and complete.\NAs a day or two went by,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.36,1:08:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the passers-by might notify the police\Nand you might get dragged off for observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.55,1:08:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's best to have somebody aware\Nthat, hey, he meditates a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.55,1:08:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYes, he meditates a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.40,1:09:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he wishes to leave the body,\Nwe will allow him to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.82,1:09:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's against Medicare rules, you know.\NI really quit going to the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.88,1:09:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nursing homes.\NI couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.20,1:09:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All these people who want to leave the body so badly.\NEverything is gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.45,1:09:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's tubes into everything.\NAnd it's on wheels.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.22,1:09:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't want to eat.\NIt's lost interest and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.22,1:09:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's please let me die is what it wants.\NSo they go, the little old lady
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.22,1:09:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can hear in any nursing home.\NHelp! Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.65,1:09:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to help us with,\Nsweetheart?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.04,1:09:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me out of here.\NIt's against the law
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.71,1:09:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow them to expire.\NAgainst their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.03,1:10:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You would think they would have the right of decision.\NNo, it's against their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.34,1:10:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to be hydrated.\NThere are tubes stuck in everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.24,1:10:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't swallow it, they'll put a tube down your...\NIt's because Medicare
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.03,1:10:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,believes that when you die, you die.\NTherefore they get excited about all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.92,1:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go from identifying\Nwith this to identifying with mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all this mental energy.\NThen you begin to intuit
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.04,1:10:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel the energy,\Nfeel the spirit around you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.56,1:10:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go of the identification with this\Nand it can happen in a sudden second.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.56,1:10:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sudden second.\NOne tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.56,1:10:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, how long does it take to get enlightened?\NOne tenth of a second, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.62,1:10:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The next instant,\Neverything has become technicolor,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.97,1:10:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,3D and incredible.\NNow, one stays in this state.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.29,1:11:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,50% never come back\Nto the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.38,1:11:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,50% never survive physically.\N50% will not
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.64,1:11:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,breathe again\Nand realize that it's idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.01,1:11:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at that point, there is no choice.\NSo when it happens, it isn't like
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.01,1:11:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a choice.\NIf enough energy gets put in from here,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.06,1:11:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you maybe get pulled back into identifying\Nwith this thinkingness here
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.06,1:11:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and fall for choice.\NSo it's best to avoid relatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.64,1:11:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One then spaces out and becomes\NI am not this, I am this.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.64,1:11:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of the self\Nis the infinite reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.04,1:11:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the very source of all of existence\Nout of which all of mankind arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.11,1:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity is the core and the essence\Nof all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.00,1:12:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much takes you out of the world\Nfor some years.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.00,1:12:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's best to have a fallback plan.\NTraditionally,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.85,1:12:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,people as they get into\Nreally serious advanced spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.85,1:12:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,have gathered together in ashrams,\Nspiritual communities.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.77,1:12:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spiritual community is the people\Nwho show up here and we know each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.77,1:12:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all know that we're involved in this.\NSo the good doctor there passes over
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.12,1:12:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,into the state of bliss.\NHis wife calls me and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.48,1:12:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, he's fine, me and Bea,\NI'll go over and enjoy with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.05,1:12:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We know each other to some degree.\NSo we don't have to congregate
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.05,1:12:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,geographically in a secluded area\Nwhich has been a traditional way of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.05,1:12:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty then,\Nit's actually not a difficulty,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.66,1:12:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with the karmic\NI guess,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.14,1:12:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, contract.\NWas it an option or a contract?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.26,1:13:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.\NIt was an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.15,1:13:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there was the option.\NThere was not the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.82,1:13:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an option.\NThere was
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.59,1:13:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the decision made\Nby the field itself
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.65,1:13:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue to exist.\NBut this
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.23,1:13:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in removal from the world\Nfor some years.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.23,1:13:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It took years to learn how to\Nrefunction again.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.90,1:13:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, even more rarely,\Nis the capacity to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.96,1:13:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,both realities\Nsimultaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.96,1:13:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to\Nbe able to relearn how to function
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.96,1:13:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world again\Nwith some physical difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.60,1:13:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the evolution\Nof consciousness as it evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.60,1:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on our planet.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.75,1:14:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll stop for a break at 10.30\Nand then we'll resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.07,1:14:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What people would like to know,\Nthey know we've calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.07,1:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the fields of consciousness,\Nwe've done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.93,1:14:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We started out to do 1,000\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.16,1:14:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we're up to 3,000 already.\NI'm not done with the list.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.51,1:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We started doing just\Nso far we've done
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.51,1:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Americana, everything from\Nrock music to movie stars.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.51,1:14:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next section has to do\Nwith spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.91,1:14:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibration of the various spiritual realities.\NThen we do countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.20,1:14:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,international, we go into\Npaleontology, archaeology,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.20,1:14:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we go\Ninto the arts, music,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.96,1:14:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,architecture, the great cathedrals,\Nplaces of great spiritual interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.25,1:15:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the lectures\NI'm sort of sharing with you
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.99,1:15:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as we get to a certain point\Nwe can make a transparency
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.05,1:15:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which is semi-legible.\NSo today we have a semi-legible transparency.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.05,1:15:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anybody got any questions\Nabout the distribution of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.98,1:15:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the implications\Nof the distribution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.98,1:15:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see it country by country,\Nregion by region,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.00,1:15:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,continent by continent.\NYou get the implications
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.04,1:15:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for how to be\Nin a world like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.61,1:15:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize\Nwhy so much diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.61,1:15:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,completely fails.\NYou just miscalculate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.03,1:15:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,where the other person is at.\NYou see, because of egotism
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.03,1:15:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody presumes that other people\Nthink like you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.03,1:15:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't think like you do at all.\NThey think the way you speak is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.28,1:16:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech is the most\Nidiotic thing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.85,1:16:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing dumber than freedom of speech.\NLet's have the percentage
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.92,1:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who think\Nthat freedom of speech is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.92,1:16:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacious.\NFallacious is over 75%,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.34,1:16:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,80%, 85%, 90%.\NFree speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.34,1:16:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,90% of free speech\Nis totally fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.30,1:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we supposed to give up our life\Nand genuflect
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.62,1:16:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because occasionally\Nsomebody tells the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.85,1:16:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,15% of the time?\NIf you tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.40,1:16:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,your butt is in hot water.\NThe editorials,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.23,1:16:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is attacking everything.\NYou calibrate the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.23,1:16:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that data\Nand now a new picture of man's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.23,1:17:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to evolve.\NTo another country,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.90,1:17:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow such disorder,\Nimagine how that's viewed
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.53,1:17:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in Singapore.\NRioting teenagers.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.87,1:17:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should they allow\Ncivil disruption
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.69,1:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and threat to the peace of the community?\NSo you see how a different community
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.69,1:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,views that.\NDabbling idiots,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.27,1:17:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,causing unrest,\Nthrowing rocks,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.56,1:17:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,starting fires,\Ncalling forth the police,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.16,1:17:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,getting arrested,\Ncausing disruption
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.28,1:17:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're\Nexpounding some ideology
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.73,1:17:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which if executed\Nwould probably kill half the population
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.96,1:17:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and usually does\Nafter the French Revolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.96,1:18:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the Russian Revolution,\Nmanage to slay most of the population.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.47,1:18:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a country then\Nin which we worship free speech,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.68,1:18:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of which is fallacious.\NStarting from a
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.22,1:18:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily fallacious position,\Nwe then seek to approach a country
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.22,1:18:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,whose calibrated level of consciousness\Nwe haven't got the slight idea about
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.28,1:18:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and even if they could understand us\Nthey would consider it ridiculous
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.28,1:18:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first place.\NYou want us to have riots in the streets,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.96,1:18:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,drugs, crime and divorce rates\N50% and a high abortion rate
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.15,1:18:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for unwedded mothers?\NWhat for?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.49,1:18:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the good of that?\NWhy should we strive and die for that?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.07,1:18:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to see what you're up against.\NWe're smugly politically superior.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.93,1:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Our system is good,\Nthe best and better
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.93,1:18:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and if other people don't like it\Nwe'll shove it down their throat
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.32,1:19:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or buy their way to it.\NSo the beginning of success
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.02,1:19:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in international affairs then\Nis by attracting
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.02,1:19:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatly successful\Npeople in society
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.02,1:19:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are based on attraction\Nand not promotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.02,1:19:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody tries to sell you anything.\NThey tell you this is how it was with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.08,1:19:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what I learned\Nand this is how my life is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.08,1:19:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound transformation.\NProbably the best example,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.08,1:19:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the most successful spiritual endeavor\Nin the world today
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.40,1:19:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably 12 step groups\Nwhere you take a hopelessly pathologic
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.40,1:19:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,condition with a 100% death rate\Nnobody ever recovered from it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.62,1:19:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with a wet brain.\NNobody ever recovered from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.78,1:19:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now millions not only recover\Nbut become very famous people
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.78,1:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,governors and statesmen\Nand great leaders of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.12,1:19:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,once had a drinking problem.\NSo the spiritual power then
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.12,1:19:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth,\Npure spiritual truth then
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.19,1:20:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is enormously powerful.\NSo the way
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.54,1:20:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we can influence other countries then\Nis through the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.73,1:20:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,through spiritual upliftment\NI saw a girl Friday
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.47,1:20:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,at a staff meeting\Nreally into apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.62,1:20:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The world would call it depression\Nand it would look for psychological reasons
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.62,1:20:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world thinks in terms of cause\Nwhat's causing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.12,1:20:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me I saw this girl\Nwho had never had energy or love
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.25,1:20:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,poured into her.\NWhere is that map of South Africa or Africa?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.25,1:20:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You still got it there?\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.92,1:20:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\NI'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.54,1:20:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to find logic or reason\Nto be of any help whatsoever
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.54,1:20:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at Energy Fuel 50.\NThis girl at the staff meeting
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.84,1:21:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have enough\Nenergy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.45,1:21:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,power of life\Nto even learn how to control
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.45,1:21:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,her bladder and her bowel.\NIt's like an infant.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.90,1:21:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the problem is not depression\Nthe problem is apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.21,1:21:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a poor energy.\NThe old lady rocking in her chair
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.43,1:21:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and she did nothing but rock back and forth\Nand look out the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.38,1:21:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She hasn't got enough energy\Nto get up and move or eat
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.41,1:21:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,get dressed.\NYou have to pour energy into them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.37,1:21:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to control myself\Nbecause I could have really
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.37,1:21:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,opened up the dams\Nand just flooded her with
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.08,1:21:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tried to give her a flash\Nas she went by
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.10,1:21:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of existence\Ncomes out of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.71,1:21:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness of the presence within.\NTo have joy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.76,1:22:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,she needs the energy of joy\Nto come out of the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.89,1:22:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm done with that one.\NLet's go back to the Calvary
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.34,1:22:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness.\NSo depression is not where she's at.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.85,1:22:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She's I'm sure here.\NApathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.40,1:22:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness.\NWhat's the point of going to school?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.40,1:22:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point of keeping your room neat?\NWhat's the point of going to the dentist?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.78,1:22:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point?\NTotal apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.32,1:22:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where South Africa is.\NHere's where that girl is.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.32,1:22:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's not South Africa\Nbut many places in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.32,1:22:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where the girl is.\NHopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.55,1:22:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She's given up.\NGod has no interest in her
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.55,1:22:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,naturally in despair.\NAnd she's into despondency.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.37,1:22:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She tries to cover it up\Nwith a certain social veneer
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.37,1:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but I see through it.\NShe's going to hold the social veneer
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.44,1:23:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as she's forced to do it.\NShe's going to pour energy into them.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.44,1:23:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the energy you pour into them?\NWell you love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.44,1:23:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You take this girl and say\NI demand that you get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.82,1:23:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she laughs.\NShe giggles.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.82,1:23:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody cares enough about her\Nto be with her in a state of joyful ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.82,1:23:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and pour forth that life energy into her.\NThe pouring forth of life energy then
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.04,1:23:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only way you can get things\Nout of the bottom of the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.04,1:23:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay so we're done with that.\NSo this sort of changes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.16,1:23:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we see international politics.\NIt means
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.71,1:23:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our first\Nthe first thing we have to do
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.80,1:23:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is we have to understand\Nwhere are they spiritually?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.80,1:23:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean in terms of\Nthe level of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.80,1:23:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the values of people at that level?\NAnd address those values.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.70,1:24:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the crime bosses\Nare so successful in poverty areas.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.08,1:24:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only source of food.\NJobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.37,1:24:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They deplore it and call them criminals.\NBut where else are they going to get a handout?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.53,1:24:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the United States\Nwe compromised didn't we
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.82,1:24:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in Afghanistan on the poppy fields.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.82,1:24:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a trade off.\NIt's cheaper to let them raise the poppy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.36,1:24:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and support themselves\Nthan to destroy the poppy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.62,1:24:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've got to put them all on welfare.\NIt seemed to me like that kind of a trade off.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.67,1:24:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Afghanistan is the source\Nof the world's supply of heroin.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.05,1:24:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The suffering and death brought about\Nby heroin worldwide
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.05,1:24:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is staggering.\NThat was the trade off.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.07,1:24:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them keep the opium fuels\Nin return for what we got for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.68,1:24:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a hard one.\NIt's like dropping an atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.68,1:24:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I didn't have to make that decision.\NThe karma of all those dying heroin addicts
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.68,1:25:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,out of there because of you.\NYour trade off.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.09,1:25:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Save the taxpayers of America the money\Nof supporting those people.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.09,1:25:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them support themselves with heroin and opium.\NSo you see how the thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.32,1:25:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the determinants of judgment,\Nmorality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.32,1:25:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the weighing of things.\NYou see it's not a matter of opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.32,1:25:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that life is a matter of subtleties.\NSlightly warmer to a little less warmer.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.32,1:25:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And a little bit more of this\Nand a little bit more of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.32,1:25:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But even when you suddenly take this direction\Nyou only did it because
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.32,1:25:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,there was one more feather.\NThe feather tipped the balance this way
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.38,1:25:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you decide to go that way.\NSo this isn't the opposite of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.44,1:25:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only one feather away.\NOne feather away.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.92,1:25:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One more feather on this side they live.\NOne more feather on this side they die.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.92,1:25:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One more feather.\NSo we hold the feathers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.44,1:25:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We hold the feathers.\NVirtually evolved people
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.56,1:26:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are the only source of real hope\Nthat people who live down here
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.69,1:26:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have.\NIt's by our pouring forth
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.95,1:26:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our concern for them.\NJust our concern for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.28,1:26:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our concern for their welfare.\NOur concern for their survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.73,1:26:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hope for their betterment.\NIt's when we send an invisible
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.76,1:26:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,love that they feel a stirring.\NYou see it's not a direct
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.76,1:26:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,cause and effect.\NYou can change the rate at which
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.21,1:26:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,something rises in water\Na cork rises in water
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.21,1:26:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing the density of the water.\NEvery swimmer knows that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.21,1:26:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You float higher in the ocean\Nthan you do in the Great Lakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.78,1:26:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up around the Great Lakes.\NNo salt in the water.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.23,1:26:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Different buoyancy.\NSo what we can do then
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.29,1:26:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is by the emanation\Nof our own divinity forth
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.68,1:26:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,our knowingness of it\Nour awareness of it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.68,1:27:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of mankind\Nwe change the specific gravity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.19,1:27:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the density\Nof the field
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.38,1:27:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore those people\Nbecome uplifted.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.41,1:27:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go there\Nand say here I want you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.60,1:27:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop being poverty\Nbecause this is food
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.67,1:27:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and now that solves it.\NNo. Keeps them alive
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.67,1:27:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can die even worse\Nat a later date doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.40,1:27:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No. One has to change\Nthe total overall context.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.40,1:27:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we demonstrated\Nin previous lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.53,1:27:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that is scientifically valid.\NIt's not hearts and flowers.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.63,1:27:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The quantum mechanics of it\Nis that decision then.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.63,1:27:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you make a decision\Nand collapse the wave function
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.36,1:27:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can change it.\NThe emanation of that
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.36,1:27:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for those of you\Nwho are interested
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.36,1:28:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the computer.\NWhat do you call that computer thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.78,1:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The e-mail world.\NInternet world, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.39,1:28:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Stapp.\NProfessor of physics at Berkeley
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.39,1:28:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,gives a very neat explanation\Ncomprehensible by the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.39,1:28:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with the opening into spiritual realities\Nand how that could manifest
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.39,1:28:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that their research\Ncan help us
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.58,1:28:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand\Nthat every time you make a decision
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.74,1:28:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in this direction\Nyou increase the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.74,1:28:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the likelihood of its recurrence.\NThere's another principle
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.74,1:28:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in quantum mechanics\Nthat the more times you say yes
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.96,1:28:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to a thing\Nyou increase the probability
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.04,1:28:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of it being yes.\NIt's not 50-50 anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.14,1:28:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it becomes higher and higher\Nprobability.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.14,1:28:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That works at a certain level.\NBut that's not going to really change things
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.33,1:29:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because when they run out of food\Nthey're right back to the same fact
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.33,1:29:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that they've got nothing to raise food on.\NWhen they run out of this bag of flour
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.33,1:29:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they're right back to starvation again.\NSo we try to lift
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.62,1:29:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of all of mankind\Nby evolving our own.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.62,1:29:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion\Nto the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.29,1:29:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nis a very powerful tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.35,1:29:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It already exists.\NYou don't have to create it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.56,1:29:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It already exists.\NThat which is willing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.22,1:29:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,everything for God\Neven life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.64,1:29:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,already exists within you.\NAnd much to your surprise
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.20,1:29:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes up in great power\Nwhen you didn't even know it was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.20,1:29:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,At the last moment\Nyou're faced with surrendering
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.20,1:30:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,life itself to God.\NTo thee, O God, do I surrender this life.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.24,1:30:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion to do so\Nis already present.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.09,1:30:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like a shock\Nwhen it comes up and you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.92,1:30:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have within you\Nthe power to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.52,1:30:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only to surrender the details of life\Nto dissolve the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.52,1:30:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend the ego\Nbut eventually the very core
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.97,1:30:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you think is you\Nas you all sit there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.37,1:30:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you profoundly believe\Nis you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.39,1:30:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,your reality\Nand who you are
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.71,1:30:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially, not intellectually\Nthat's the doorway
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.60,1:30:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,one surrenders completely.\NAnd that is the doorway to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.58,1:31:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the limitation\Nof the commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.92,1:31:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't happen all that often.\NDevotional non-duality means
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.68,1:31:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,one is devoted to the truth\Ndevoted to the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.68,1:31:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll get to more of the truth\Nafter we have a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.92,1:31:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is necessary\Nto reach enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.80,1:31:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,already exists.\NTo reach a state of divine
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.60,1:31:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional lovingness\Nis quite sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.60,1:31:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nthe Lotusland Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.60,1:31:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which teaches pretty much the same\Nas Christianity then says
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.70,1:31:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,once you've reached the level of unconditional love\Nthe way is certain
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.70,1:31:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can relax.\NAnd so we'll take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.04,1:32:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have read\Nthe books and attended lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.77,1:32:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,know that the pathway\Nthe direct pathway to God is radical.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.32,1:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a radical devotion\Nto truth above all else.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.72,1:32:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that so important?\NBecause untruth stands
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.43,1:33:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the way of love\Nand those who seek to reach God through love
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.43,1:33:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly run into blocks.\NSo we try to resolve the blocks
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.87,1:33:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when devotion\Ncomes up there's nothing to obstruct it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.14,1:33:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it does it comes like\Nlike a dam just broke
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.24,1:33:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no stopping it.\NSo we'll get rid of duality
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.99,1:33:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,today and the next\Nless than a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.04,1:33:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because\Nyou like chocolate doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.93,1:33:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to hate vanilla.\NThat resolves all your political problems
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.16,1:33:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,right there.\NSome people like chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.87,1:33:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some people like vanilla.\NWe don't have to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.40,1:34:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have\Nto kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.15,1:34:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way, the fastest way\Nto reach the presence within
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.40,1:34:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is through joy.\NJoy, happiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.45,1:34:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thankfulness, gratitude,\Ngoodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.72,1:34:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hear those are all positive things.\NThat's different than
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.80,1:34:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth and ashes,\Nself-flagellation, agony, suffering,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.80,1:34:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sin. It's a different pathway.\NYou're welcome
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.88,1:34:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to it if you wish.\NIt's certainly why I became
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.40,1:34:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,an atheist when I was a young age.\NNo, because it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.48,1:34:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,conflicted with an inner knowingness\Nof the truth that the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.48,1:35:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with that which is\Necstatic, exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.48,1:35:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,joyful.\NSo we look at the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.84,1:35:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,antecedent of it. We looked at the world\Ntoday and we see how it's laid out at this point
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.84,1:35:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the advancement of evolution.\NWe see the distribution of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.32,1:35:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. You understand\Nthe profundity of the discovery
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.18,1:35:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because we can take\Nthe calibrated levels of consciousness of every
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.76,1:35:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,country and every region.\NWe can do that with every
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.76,1:35:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,antecedent of man, Neanderthal man,\NHomo erectus.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.76,1:35:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This week's Time magazine\Nhad a new one, 160,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.20,1:35:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't calibrate\Nhis level of consciousness yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.29,1:35:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We will do so now.\NHe is an antecedent.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.33,1:35:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.\NHe is an antecedent of Homo sapiens.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.59,1:36:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And he is an early Homo sapiens.\NAnd his consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.67,1:36:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 100.\NHis consciousness is over 70.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.88,1:36:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,His consciousness is over\N65.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.84,1:36:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His consciousness is over 60.\NHis consciousness is over 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.48,1:36:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He better get up there.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.71,1:36:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see the beginning of the structure\Nof Homo sapiens.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.71,1:36:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then consciousness catches up with it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.28,1:36:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa.\NOh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.18,1:36:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with the calibrated levels\Nof consciousness is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.01,1:36:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it can get you into a polarized position\Nof that which makes you go weak,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.01,1:37:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that which makes you go strong,\Nthat which is below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.01,1:37:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is over.\NThe truth versus falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.41,1:37:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the downside of it.\NSo that's why I mentioned chocolate and vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.41,1:37:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you like chocolate.\NIt doesn't mean you have to make vanilla wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.48,1:37:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because vanilla had to first become vanilla\Nbefore it could become chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.88,1:37:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to have ice cream before you could flavor it.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.39,1:37:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So vanilla is below 200.\NIt's early antecedent Homo sapiens.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.39,1:37:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he rises\Nin his level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.39,1:37:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it becomes chocolate.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.08,1:37:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to get out of polarization.\NRemember chocolate and vanilla
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.08,1:37:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it will get you right out of it.\NYou'll see that your mind is automatically reverting back to
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.08,1:37:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we're right therefore they're wrong.\NNo, they like chocolate, we like vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.59,1:38:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We as societies think that free speech is idiotic.\NIt leads to insurrection.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.84,1:38:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads to death.\NIt leads to revolt.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.28,1:38:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads to destruction of the economy.\NSo you see
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.13,1:38:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they like chocolate and we like vanilla.\NWe want to feel that you can blabber anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.13,1:38:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is entertaining.\NI mean our country is more entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.06,1:38:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can only say what's been approved\Nhow tedious, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.32,1:38:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now\Nthe books I've written are being looked at
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.96,1:38:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in China and they have a thought police there\Nthey have to examine them and see
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.96,1:38:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not they're permissible\Nto publish in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.40,1:38:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're hoping that they won't notice\Nspiritual and religious and they just pay attention
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.40,1:38:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness.\NConsciousness may slip by the censors.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.40,1:39:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so today I thought we would\Nshare where we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.70,1:39:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see you can go back now in the maps\Nthat we have and check them out
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.70,1:39:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,century by century.\NTake this whole map.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.76,1:39:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to picture this.\NThis is a wonderment of movies
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.89,1:39:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hologram.\NLet's say each one of those calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.31,1:39:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has a color.\NIt gets darker and lighter let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.31,1:39:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Or more green and more yellow.\NAnd you go back 500 years
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.11,1:39:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and do these same areas.\NYou go back another 100 years and do the same areas.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.11,1:39:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You go back and back and back through time.\NSee what a fascinating map that would make?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.45,1:39:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,First you see light begin to appear.\NThen it comes out light yellow.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.45,1:39:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it starts to turn green.\NAnd over here you see it turn red.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.45,1:39:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it turns black.\NAnd here it shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.86,1:39:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,like a moving hologram over time.\NSee what you can do with that with graphics.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.24,1:40:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the technology exists to do it.\NSo what were the levels of these countries
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.10,1:40:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,century by century?\NAnd you can see the
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.96,1:40:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,men begin to appear.\NHomo sapiens begin to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.96,1:40:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the consciousness level\Nappear and then you see it shine forth
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.40,1:40:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,most brilliantly in today's world\Nin North America
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.40,1:40:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and in America in particular.\NYou might say
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.79,1:40:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we're the advancing front\Nof the evolution of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.79,1:40:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates higher than any country.\NWhich means
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.46,1:40:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that we don't like idiots.\NIt's just that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.44,1:40:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,vanilla and chocolate is mixed together\Nso you get mocha.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.87,1:40:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the difference is that\Nthe reason I said
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.60,1:40:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the best thing we can do for the world\Nis to hold them in our thoughts and prayers
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.89,1:41:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is because\Nthe higher the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.15,1:41:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater its power.\NSo numerically
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.56,1:41:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be many below 200\Nbut their relative power
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.63,1:41:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is weak because\None person at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.72,1:41:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances\Nmost of humanity
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.72,1:41:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and one at 1000\Nreally counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.72,1:41:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,all of mankind.\NSo consequently
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.85,1:41:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the more advanced we become\Nand hold such people in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.85,1:41:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,compassionate\Nfor their suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.56,1:41:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then the power of that intention\Nis such that we actually
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.56,1:41:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,lift the life of people\Nat the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.87,1:41:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true\Nor if that's airy-fairy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.08,1:41:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sedona doesn't like airy-fairy.\NSo we just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.08,1:42:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion of even a group like this\Nwill have a measurable effect
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.20,1:42:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on the consciousness level\Nof those at the bottom of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.20,1:42:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness of this group\Nhere
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.73,1:42:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,affects those at the bottom of the barrel.\NOne day
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.47,1:42:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of not having the energy\Nto even feed yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.50,1:42:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you care enough to feed yourself.\NMany at the bottom of the barrel
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.92,1:42:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,do not even have the energy\Nto feed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.92,1:42:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They will starve to death\Nlaying right next to the food.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.58,1:42:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe but it's so.\NSo if we include them
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.58,1:42:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in our intention\Nand spiritual intention is where your power is
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.71,1:42:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that will save you flying over there\Nand marching in parades
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.68,1:42:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you affect the field\Nand because you affect the field
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.68,1:42:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you affect that which is real.\NThat which is real. That which is permanent.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.16,1:43:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has great power.\NAlright, so we just transcended
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.95,1:43:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and the intellect\Nand we did a lot already.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.01,1:43:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see how this\Nevolved over time
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.01,1:43:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because we also\Ncalibrated, I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.27,1:43:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,like about 600\Nspiritual teachers, religions
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.27,1:43:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,things that\NI get a constant mail
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.65,1:43:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about these things\Nand therefore we thought we'd do some.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.65,1:43:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start with one.\NPeople ask, you know
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.87,1:43:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,endlessly. We've got stacks\Nof mail this high.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.57,1:43:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This teacher, that guru, that book\Nthis spiritual discipline,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.83,1:43:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this religion. Now where do they\Ncalibrate? Well
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.02,1:43:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we've reached the\Nat least this group has reached the level
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.02,1:43:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of dedication to truth.\NSo I'll give you a caveat.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.24,1:44:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who belongs to a\Nrigid religion, you better
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.07,1:44:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,leave now. Alright, so we\Nbegan calibrating
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.18,1:44:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we all start out\Nin the same place as
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.40,1:44:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nature of God.\NIn the book I, I think
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.17,1:44:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we summarized what we did at Creative Life\NI think chapter 10 calibrates it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.17,1:44:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand. The exact nature\Nof God. I think we made 24
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.88,1:44:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or 28 statements about the exact nature\Nof God. In the entire group
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.88,1:44:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we all did kinesiology together\Nand there was 100%
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.58,1:44:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement about the truth of every single\Nstatement, which is videotaped
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.80,1:44:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,documented forever.\NSo you don't have to go back to scriptures that
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.47,1:44:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are a thousand years old\Nall about dead people and geographic
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.47,1:45:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,places you're never going to visit and never have been.\NThe evidence for the existence
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.84,1:45:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reality of God is right here\Nnow. Right here now.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.09,1:45:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to rely on\Nhistory. Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.40,1:45:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So to make sure we're all in the same\Nplace, we have to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.40,1:45:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what we mean by God and so we asked\Nwhat are the various names of God
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.40,1:45:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do they calibrate?\NThe verification of spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.04,1:45:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Man has had no way to verify\Nspiritual reality. The only person who can
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.38,1:45:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,verify spiritual reality is a mystic.\NEverybody else is just talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.38,1:45:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What they heard, what they read in\Nsome old book. What good does that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.16,1:45:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,do you? You don't get enlightened\N2000 years back in retrospect.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.70,1:45:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens here now folks.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.70,1:45:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God has to be an\Nexistent, verifiable,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.70,1:46:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential, subjective\Nreality which can
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.02,1:46:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,be experienced in the here and now.\NOtherwise it's just talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.02,1:46:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is full of talking\Nabout God. Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.43,1:46:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we said what is\Nthe energy field of
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.78,1:46:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the concept of God transcendent?\NWhat's
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.68,1:46:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God infinity, the creator?\NAlmighty God.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.42,1:46:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Creator of heaven and earth\Nand of all things visible and invisible
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.42,1:46:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,through his son our Lord Jesus Christ\Nand the Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.42,1:46:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We do bless this endeavor. Amen.\NAll those terms are infinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.34,1:46:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The supreme,\Nwhich you hear from Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.79,1:46:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The supreme, Allah, the God of\NMuslims, Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.01,1:46:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Brahman, all the names for God,\NVishnu. You ask what do they
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.01,1:47:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate? God of Moses\Nand I wrote that in.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.52,1:47:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't want to forget\NAbraham. All of them
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.64,1:47:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,infinity. Okay.\NSo that is God as transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.64,1:47:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite creator\Nof all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.02,1:47:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest becoming manifest\Nas creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.14,1:47:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite energy field\Nto which all form
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.99,1:47:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,responds automatically\Nas a quality
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.63,1:47:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own existence.\NGod is imminent then
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.16,1:47:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is the God of the mystic.\NThe one that we strive
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.06,1:47:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for in these classes.\NIt's referred to
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.63,1:47:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in Sanskrit as God imminent\Nas the Purusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.72,1:47:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As a spiritual teacher is talking\Nonce comes the wording,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.72,1:48:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding, the conceptualization,\Netc. It happens
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.72,1:48:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously of its own.\NThere is no decision or thought about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.78,1:48:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To use a bad word\Nis not a decision one makes
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.68,1:48:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when hears it.\NIt was just
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.28,1:48:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,said. Oh, okay.\NIt's happening of its own spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.02,1:48:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you reach a certain\Nlevel of realization
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.53,1:48:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that\Nthat is the state of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.53,1:48:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists at all times.\NThere is no you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.72,1:48:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,deciding to sit in the chair\Nor trying to understand this
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.72,1:48:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or think your thoughts.\NIt's happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.68,1:48:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You as this little iron filing\Nthrough your own spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.68,1:48:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,bring yourself into a certain field\Nin which all that phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.68,1:48:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening autonomously,\Nautomatically, and perfectly of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.96,1:49:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't require you to even do that.\NThat gets rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.71,1:49:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that there is a person\Nspeaking all these words
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.71,1:49:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the height of success of the ego.\NThe ego would say,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.03,1:49:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the author of all that you do think\Nand experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.03,1:49:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is not the author of experience.\NIt's something
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.32,1:49:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that gets filtered through.\NSo, the self
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.92,1:49:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we hear the realization of the self\Nmany spiritual treatises
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.92,1:49:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are called realization of the self.\NThe self with a capital S then
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.46,1:49:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is God immanent, present\Nand it speaks as the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.46,1:49:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Purusha of the teacher.\NIt speaks as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.81,1:49:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's merely the voice.\NAnother term for it is Atman.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.88,1:49:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this\Nis supposed to be down below here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.36,1:49:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I want to contrast\NGod immanent and transcendent
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.84,1:50:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is great argumentation.\NThe Catholic Church is divided
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.93,1:50:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,East and West, the Greek Orthodox\Nand the Roman Church
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.16,1:50:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,over the understanding of\Nsome of these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.28,1:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So they are very divisive\Nwhether the ultimate reality is
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.28,1:50:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God transcendent or\NGod immanent
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.28,1:50:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can lead to huge schisms within the church.\NAnd in reality
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.28,1:50:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't experience God as transcendent.\NYou can only
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.80,1:50:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experience God as immanent.\NYou can talk about God as transcendent
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.80,1:50:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore theology goes up to about\N460 and then it stops there.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.18,1:50:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So theology\Nhas perfected the talking-ness about it
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.18,1:50:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and\None of the ways to God is through philosophy
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.68,1:50:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you are serious about philosophy\Nit will take you to epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.68,1:50:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Epistemology will take you\Nto the transference
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.70,1:50:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the source of the reality\Nof the source of the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.73,1:51:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality from objective to subjective\Nand there you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.73,1:51:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can find God if you\Nfollow philosophy to its bitter end
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.66,1:51:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,where you finally give up classical\Nphilosophy and you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.69,1:51:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that only subjectivity\Ncan be verified.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.64,1:51:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One cannot verify\Nany objectivity at all
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.05,1:51:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere.
